70static Element* elementOrPseudoElementForStyleable(const std::optional<const Styleable>& styleable)
71{
72 if (!styleable)
73 return nullptr;
74
75 switch (styleable->pseudoId) {
76 case PseudoId::Before:
77 return styleable->element.beforePseudoElement();
78 case PseudoId::After:
79 return styleable->element.afterPseudoElement();
80 default:
81 return &styleable->element;
82 }
83}
84
85static inline void invalidateElement(const std::optional<const Styleable>& styleable)
86{
87 if (auto* elementOrPseudoElement = elementOrPseudoElementForStyleable(styleable))
88 elementOrPseudoElement->invalidateStyleInternal();
89}

91static inline String CSSPropertyIDToIDLAttributeName(CSSPropertyID cssPropertyId)
92{
93 // https://drafts.csswg.org/web-animations-1/#animation-property-name-to-idl-attribute-name
94 // 1. If property follows the <custom-property-name> production, return property.
95 // FIXME: We don't handle custom properties yet.
96
97 // 2. If property refers to the CSS float property, return the string "cssFloat".
98 if (cssPropertyId == CSSPropertyFloat)
99 return "cssFloat";
100
101 // 3. If property refers to the CSS offset property, return the string "cssOffset".
102 // FIXME: we don't support the CSS "offset" property
103
104 // 4. Otherwise, return the result of applying the CSS property to IDL attribute algorithm [CSSOM] to property.
105 return getJSPropertyName(cssPropertyId);
106}
107
108static inline CSSPropertyID IDLAttributeNameToAnimationPropertyName(const String& idlAttributeName)
109{
110 // https://drafts.csswg.org/web-animations-1/#idl-attribute-name-to-animation-property-name
111 // 1. If attribute conforms to the <custom-property-name> production, return attribute.
112 // FIXME: We don't handle custom properties yet.
113
114 // 2. If attribute is the string "cssFloat", then return an animation property representing the CSS float property.
115 if (idlAttributeName == "cssFloat")
116 return CSSPropertyFloat;
117
118 // 3. If attribute is the string "cssOffset", then return an animation property representing the CSS offset property.
119 // FIXME: We don't support the CSS "offset" property.
120
121 // 4. Otherwise, return the result of applying the IDL attribute to CSS property algorithm [CSSOM] to attribute.
122 auto cssPropertyId = CSSStyleDeclaration::getCSSPropertyIDFromJavaScriptPropertyName(idlAttributeName);
123
124 // We need to check that converting the property back to IDL form yields the same result such that a property passed
125 // in non-IDL form is rejected, for instance "font-size".
126 if (idlAttributeName != CSSPropertyIDToIDLAttributeName(cssPropertyId))
127 return CSSPropertyInvalid;
128
129 return cssPropertyId;
130}
131
132static inline void computeMissingKeyframeOffsets(Vector<KeyframeEffect::ParsedKeyframe>& keyframes)
133{
134 // https://drafts.csswg.org/web-animations-1/#compute-missing-keyframe-offsets
135
136 if (keyframes.isEmpty())
137 return;
138
139 // 1. For each keyframe, in keyframes, let the computed keyframe offset of the keyframe be equal to its keyframe offset value.
140 // In our implementation, we only set non-null values to avoid making computedOffset std::optional<double>. Instead, we'll know
141 // that a keyframe hasn't had a computed offset by checking if it has a null offset and a 0 computedOffset, since the first
142 // keyframe will already have a 0 computedOffset.
143 for (auto& keyframe : keyframes) {
144 auto computedOffset = keyframe.offset;
145 keyframe.computedOffset = computedOffset ? *computedOffset : 0;
146 }
147
148 // 2. If keyframes contains more than one keyframe and the computed keyframe offset of the first keyframe in keyframes is null,
149 // set the computed keyframe offset of the first keyframe to 0.
150 if (keyframes.size() > 1 && !keyframes[0].offset)
151 keyframes[0].computedOffset = 0;
152
153 // 3. If the computed keyframe offset of the last keyframe in keyframes is null, set its computed keyframe offset to 1.
154 if (!keyframes.last().offset)
155 keyframes.last().computedOffset = 1;
156
157 // 4. For each pair of keyframes A and B where:
158 // - A appears before B in keyframes, and
159 // - A and B have a computed keyframe offset that is not null, and
160 // - all keyframes between A and B have a null computed keyframe offset,
161 // calculate the computed keyframe offset of each keyframe between A and B as follows:
162 // 1. Let offsetk be the computed keyframe offset of a keyframe k.
163 // 2. Let n be the number of keyframes between and including A and B minus 1.
164 // 3. Let index refer to the position of keyframe in the sequence of keyframes between A and B such that the first keyframe after A has an index of 1.
165 // 4. Set the computed keyframe offset of keyframe to offsetA + (offsetB − offsetA) × index / n.
166 size_t indexOfLastKeyframeWithNonNullOffset = 0;
167 for (size_t i = 1; i < keyframes.size(); ++i) {
168 auto& keyframe = keyframes[i];
169 // Keyframes with a null offset that don't yet have a non-zero computed offset are keyframes
170 // with an offset that needs to be computed.
171 if (!keyframe.offset && !keyframe.computedOffset)
172 continue;
173 if (indexOfLastKeyframeWithNonNullOffset != i - 1) {
174 double lastNonNullOffset = keyframes[indexOfLastKeyframeWithNonNullOffset].computedOffset;
175 double offsetDelta = keyframe.computedOffset - lastNonNullOffset;
176 double offsetIncrement = offsetDelta / (i - indexOfLastKeyframeWithNonNullOffset);
177 size_t indexOfFirstKeyframeWithNullOffset = indexOfLastKeyframeWithNonNullOffset + 1;
178 for (size_t j = indexOfFirstKeyframeWithNullOffset; j < i; ++j)
179 keyframes[j].computedOffset = lastNonNullOffset + (j - indexOfLastKeyframeWithNonNullOffset) * offsetIncrement;
180 }
181 indexOfLastKeyframeWithNonNullOffset = i;
182 }
183}

185static inline ExceptionOr<KeyframeEffect::KeyframeLikeObject> processKeyframeLikeObject(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, Strong<JSObject>&& keyframesInput, bool allowLists)
186{
187 // https://drafts.csswg.org/web-animations-1/#process-a-keyframe-like-object
188
189 VM& vm = lexicalGlobalObject.vm();
190 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
191
192 // 1. Run the procedure to convert an ECMAScript value to a dictionary type [WEBIDL] with keyframe input as the ECMAScript value as follows:
193 //
194 // If allow lists is true, use the following dictionary type:
195 //
196 // dictionary BasePropertyIndexedKeyframe {
197 // (double? or sequence<double?>) offset = [];
198 // (DOMString or sequence<DOMString>) easing = [];
199 // (CompositeOperationOrAuto or sequence<CompositeOperationOrAuto>) composite = [];
200 // };
201 //
202 // Otherwise, use the following dictionary type:
203 //
204 // dictionary BaseKeyframe {
205 // double? offset = null;
206 // DOMString easing = "linear";
207 // CompositeOperationOrAuto composite = "auto";
208 // };
209 //
210 // Store the result of this procedure as keyframe output.
211 KeyframeEffect::BasePropertyIndexedKeyframe baseProperties;
212 if (allowLists)
213 baseProperties = convert<IDLDictionary<KeyframeEffect::BasePropertyIndexedKeyframe>>(lexicalGlobalObject, keyframesInput.get());
214 else {
215 auto baseKeyframe = convert<IDLDictionary<KeyframeEffect::BaseKeyframe>>(lexicalGlobalObject, keyframesInput.get());
216 if (baseKeyframe.offset)
217 baseProperties.offset = baseKeyframe.offset.value();
218 else
219 baseProperties.offset = nullptr;
220 baseProperties.easing = baseKeyframe.easing;
221
222 auto* scriptExecutionContext = jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(&lexicalGlobalObject)->scriptExecutionContext();
223 if (is<Document>(scriptExecutionContext)) {
224 if (downcast<Document>(*scriptExecutionContext).settings().webAnimationsCompositeOperationsEnabled())
225 baseProperties.composite = baseKeyframe.composite;
226 }
227 }
228 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, Exception { TypeError });
229
230 KeyframeEffect::KeyframeLikeObject keyframeOuput;
231 keyframeOuput.baseProperties = baseProperties;
232
233 // 2. Build up a list of animatable properties as follows:
234 //
235 // 1. Let animatable properties be a list of property names (including shorthand properties that have longhand sub-properties
236 // that are animatable) that can be animated by the implementation.
237 // 2. Convert each property name in animatable properties to the equivalent IDL attribute by applying the animation property
238 // name to IDL attribute name algorithm.
239
240 // 3. Let input properties be the result of calling the EnumerableOwnNames operation with keyframe input as the object.
241 PropertyNameArray inputProperties(vm, PropertyNameMode::Strings, PrivateSymbolMode::Exclude);
242 JSObject::getOwnPropertyNames(keyframesInput.get(), &lexicalGlobalObject, inputProperties, DontEnumPropertiesMode::Exclude);
243
244 // 4. Make up a new list animation properties that consists of all of the properties that are in both input properties and animatable
245 // properties, or which are in input properties and conform to the <custom-property-name> production.
246 Vector<JSC::Identifier> animationProperties;
247 size_t numberOfProperties = inputProperties.size();
248 for (size_t i = 0; i < numberOfProperties; ++i) {
249 if (CSSPropertyAnimation::isPropertyAnimatable(IDLAttributeNameToAnimationPropertyName(inputProperties[i].string())))
250 animationProperties.append(inputProperties[i]);
251 }
252
253 // 5. Sort animation properties in ascending order by the Unicode codepoints that define each property name.
254 std::sort(animationProperties.begin(), animationProperties.end(), [](auto& lhs, auto& rhs) {
255 return lhs.string().utf8() < rhs.string().utf8();
256 });
257
258 // 6. For each property name in animation properties,
259 size_t numberOfAnimationProperties = animationProperties.size();
260 for (size_t i = 0; i < numberOfAnimationProperties; ++i) {
261 // 1. Let raw value be the result of calling the [[Get]] internal method on keyframe input, with property name as the property
262 // key and keyframe input as the receiver.
263 auto rawValue = keyframesInput->get(&lexicalGlobalObject, animationProperties[i]);
264
265 // 2. Check the completion record of raw value.
266 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, Exception { TypeError });
267
268 // 3. Convert raw value to a DOMString or sequence of DOMStrings property values as follows:
269 Vector<String> propertyValues;
270 if (allowLists) {
271 // If allow lists is true,
272 // Let property values be the result of converting raw value to IDL type (DOMString or sequence<DOMString>)
273 // using the procedures defined for converting an ECMAScript value to an IDL value [WEBIDL].
274 // If property values is a single DOMString, replace property values with a sequence of DOMStrings with the original value of property
275 // Values as the only element.
276 if (rawValue.isObject())
277 propertyValues = convert<IDLSequence<IDLDOMString>>(lexicalGlobalObject, rawValue);
278 else
279 propertyValues = { rawValue.toWTFString(&lexicalGlobalObject) };
280 } else {
281 // Otherwise,
282 // Let property values be the result of converting raw value to a DOMString using the procedure for converting an ECMAScript value to a DOMString.
283 propertyValues = { convert<IDLDOMString>(lexicalGlobalObject, rawValue) };
284 }
285 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, Exception { TypeError });
286
287 // 4. Calculate the normalized property name as the result of applying the IDL attribute name to animation property name algorithm to property name.
288 auto cssPropertyID = IDLAttributeNameToAnimationPropertyName(animationProperties[i].string());
289
290 // 5. Add a property to to keyframe output with normalized property name as the property name, and property values as the property value.
291 keyframeOuput.propertiesAndValues.append({ cssPropertyID, propertyValues });
292 }
293
294 // 7. Return keyframe output.
295 return { WTFMove(keyframeOuput) };
296}

298static inline ExceptionOr<void> processIterableKeyframes(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, Strong<JSObject>&& keyframesInput, JSValue method, Vector<KeyframeEffect::ParsedKeyframe>& parsedKeyframes)
299{
300 auto* scriptExecutionContext = jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(&lexicalGlobalObject)->scriptExecutionContext();
301 if (!is<Document>(scriptExecutionContext))
302 return { };
303 auto& document = downcast<Document>(*scriptExecutionContext);
304 CSSParserContext parserContext(document);
305
306 // 1. Let iter be GetIterator(object, method).
307 forEachInIterable(lexicalGlobalObject, keyframesInput.get(), method, [&parsedKeyframes, &document, &parserContext](VM& vm, JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, JSValue nextValue) -> ExceptionOr<void> {
308 // Steps 2 through 6 are already implemented by forEachInIterable().
309 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
310 if (!nextValue || !nextValue.isObject()) {
311 throwException(&lexicalGlobalObject, scope, JSC::Exception::create(vm, createTypeError(&lexicalGlobalObject)));
312 return { };
313 }
314
315 // 7. Append to processed keyframes the result of running the procedure to process a keyframe-like object passing nextItem
316 // as the keyframe input and with the allow lists flag set to false.
317 auto processKeyframeLikeObjectResult = processKeyframeLikeObject(lexicalGlobalObject, Strong<JSObject>(vm, nextValue.toObject(&lexicalGlobalObject)), false);
318 if (processKeyframeLikeObjectResult.hasException())
319 return processKeyframeLikeObjectResult.releaseException();
320 auto keyframeLikeObject = processKeyframeLikeObjectResult.returnValue();
321
322 KeyframeEffect::ParsedKeyframe keyframeOutput;
323
324 // When calling processKeyframeLikeObject() with the "allow lists" flag set to false, the only offset
325 // alternatives we should expect are double and nullptr.
326 if (WTF::holds_alternative<double>(keyframeLikeObject.baseProperties.offset))
327 keyframeOutput.offset = WTF::get<double>(keyframeLikeObject.baseProperties.offset);
328 else
329 ASSERT(WTF::holds_alternative<std::nullptr_t>(keyframeLikeObject.baseProperties.offset));
330
331 // When calling processKeyframeLikeObject() with the "allow lists" flag set to false, the only easing
332 // alternative we should expect is String.
333 ASSERT(WTF::holds_alternative<String>(keyframeLikeObject.baseProperties.easing));
334 keyframeOutput.easing = WTF::get<String>(keyframeLikeObject.baseProperties.easing);
335
336 // When calling processKeyframeLikeObject() with the "allow lists" flag set to false, the only composite
337 // alternatives we should expect is CompositeOperationAuto.
338 if (document.settings().webAnimationsCompositeOperationsEnabled()) {
339 ASSERT(WTF::holds_alternative<CompositeOperationOrAuto>(keyframeLikeObject.baseProperties.composite));
340 keyframeOutput.composite = WTF::get<CompositeOperationOrAuto>(keyframeLikeObject.baseProperties.composite);
341 }
342
343 for (auto& propertyAndValue : keyframeLikeObject.propertiesAndValues) {
344 auto cssPropertyId = propertyAndValue.property;
345 // When calling processKeyframeLikeObject() with the "allow lists" flag set to false,
346 // there should only ever be a single value for a given property.
347 ASSERT(propertyAndValue.values.size() == 1);
348 auto stringValue = propertyAndValue.values[0];
349 if (keyframeOutput.style->setProperty(cssPropertyId, stringValue, false, parserContext))
350 keyframeOutput.unparsedStyle.set(cssPropertyId, stringValue);
351 }
352
353 parsedKeyframes.append(WTFMove(keyframeOutput));
354
355 return { };
356 });
357
358 return { };
359}

361static inline ExceptionOr<void> processPropertyIndexedKeyframes(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, Strong<JSObject>&& keyframesInput, Vector<KeyframeEffect::ParsedKeyframe>& parsedKeyframes, Vector<String>& unusedEasings)
362{
363 // 1. Let property-indexed keyframe be the result of running the procedure to process a keyframe-like object passing object as the keyframe input.
364 auto processKeyframeLikeObjectResult = processKeyframeLikeObject(lexicalGlobalObject, WTFMove(keyframesInput), true);
365 if (processKeyframeLikeObjectResult.hasException())
366 return processKeyframeLikeObjectResult.releaseException();
367 auto propertyIndexedKeyframe = processKeyframeLikeObjectResult.returnValue();
368
369 auto* scriptExecutionContext = jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(&lexicalGlobalObject)->scriptExecutionContext();
370 if (!is<Document>(scriptExecutionContext))
371 return { };
372 auto& document = downcast<Document>(*scriptExecutionContext);
373 CSSParserContext parserContext(document);
374
375 // 2. For each member, m, in property-indexed keyframe, perform the following steps:
376 for (auto& m : propertyIndexedKeyframe.propertiesAndValues) {
377 // 1. Let property name be the key for m.
378 auto propertyName = m.property;
379 // 2. If property name is “composite”, or “easing”, or “offset”, skip the remaining steps in this loop and continue from the next member in property-indexed
380 // keyframe after m.
381 // We skip this test since we split those properties and the actual CSS properties that we're currently iterating over.
382 // 3. Let property values be the value for m.
383 auto propertyValues = m.values;
384 // 4. Let property keyframes be an empty sequence of keyframes.
385 Vector<KeyframeEffect::ParsedKeyframe> propertyKeyframes;
386 // 5. For each value, v, in property values perform the following steps:
387 for (auto& v : propertyValues) {
388 // 1. Let k be a new keyframe with a null keyframe offset.
389 KeyframeEffect::ParsedKeyframe k;
390 // 2. Add the property-value pair, property name → v, to k.
391 if (k.style->setProperty(propertyName, v, false, parserContext))
392 k.unparsedStyle.set(propertyName, v);
393 // 3. Append k to property keyframes.
394 propertyKeyframes.append(WTFMove(k));
395 }
396 // 6. Apply the procedure to compute missing keyframe offsets to property keyframes.
397 computeMissingKeyframeOffsets(propertyKeyframes);
398
399 // 7. Add keyframes in property keyframes to processed keyframes.
400 for (auto& keyframe : propertyKeyframes)
401 parsedKeyframes.append(WTFMove(keyframe));
402 }
403
404 // 3. Sort processed keyframes by the computed keyframe offset of each keyframe in increasing order.
405 std::sort(parsedKeyframes.begin(), parsedKeyframes.end(), [](auto& lhs, auto& rhs) {
406 return lhs.computedOffset < rhs.computedOffset;
407 });
408
409 // 4. Merge adjacent keyframes in processed keyframes when they have equal computed keyframe offsets.
410 size_t i = 1;
411 while (i < parsedKeyframes.size()) {
412 auto& keyframe = parsedKeyframes[i];
413 auto& previousKeyframe = parsedKeyframes[i - 1];
414 // If the offsets of this keyframe and the previous keyframe are different,
415 // this means that the two keyframes should not be merged and we can move
416 // on to the next keyframe.
417 if (keyframe.computedOffset != previousKeyframe.computedOffset) {
418 i++;
419 continue;
420 }
421 // Otherwise, both this keyframe and the previous keyframe should be merged.
422 // Unprocessed keyframes in parsedKeyframes at this stage have at most a single
423 // property in cssPropertiesAndValues, so just set this on the previous keyframe.
424 // In case an invalid or null value was originally provided, then the property
425 // was not set and the property count is 0, in which case there is nothing to merge.
426 if (keyframe.style->propertyCount()) {
427 auto property = keyframe.style->propertyAt(0);
428 previousKeyframe.style->setProperty(property.id(), property.value());
429 previousKeyframe.unparsedStyle.set(property.id(), keyframe.unparsedStyle.get(property.id()));
430 }
431 // Since we've processed this keyframe, we can remove it and keep i the same
432 // so that we process the next keyframe in the next loop iteration.
433 parsedKeyframes.remove(i);
434 }
435
436 // 5. Let offsets be a sequence of nullable double values assigned based on the type of the “offset” member of the property-indexed keyframe as follows:
437 // - sequence<double?>, the value of “offset” as-is.
438 // - double?, a sequence of length one with the value of “offset” as its single item, i.e. « offset »,
439 Vector<std::optional<double>> offsets;
440 if (WTF::holds_alternative<Vector<std::optional<double>>>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.offset))
441 offsets = WTF::get<Vector<std::optional<double>>>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.offset);
442 else if (WTF::holds_alternative<double>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.offset))
443 offsets.append(WTF::get<double>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.offset));
444 else if (WTF::holds_alternative<std::nullptr_t>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.offset))
445 offsets.append(std::nullopt);
446
447 // 6. Assign each value in offsets to the keyframe offset of the keyframe with corresponding position in property keyframes until the end of either sequence is reached.
448 for (size_t i = 0; i < offsets.size() && i < parsedKeyframes.size(); ++i)
449 parsedKeyframes[i].offset = offsets[i];
450
451 // 7. Let easings be a sequence of DOMString values assigned based on the type of the “easing” member of the property-indexed keyframe as follows:
452 // - sequence<DOMString>, the value of “easing” as-is.
453 // - DOMString, a sequence of length one with the value of “easing” as its single item, i.e. « easing »,
454 Vector<String> easings;
455 if (WTF::holds_alternative<Vector<String>>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.easing))
456 easings = WTF::get<Vector<String>>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.easing);
457 else if (WTF::holds_alternative<String>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.easing))
458 easings.append(WTF::get<String>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.easing));
459
460 // 8. If easings is an empty sequence, let it be a sequence of length one containing the single value “linear”, i.e. « "linear" ».
461 if (easings.isEmpty())
462 easings.append("linear");
463
464 // 9. If easings has fewer items than property keyframes, repeat the elements in easings successively starting from the beginning of the list until easings has as many
465 // items as property keyframes.
466 if (easings.size() < parsedKeyframes.size()) {
467 size_t initialNumberOfEasings = easings.size();
468 for (i = initialNumberOfEasings; i < parsedKeyframes.size(); ++i)
469 easings.append(easings[i % initialNumberOfEasings]);
470 }
471
472 // 10. If easings has more items than property keyframes, store the excess items as unused easings.
473 while (easings.size() > parsedKeyframes.size())
474 unusedEasings.append(easings.takeLast());
475
476 // 11. Assign each value in easings to a property named “easing” on the keyframe with the corresponding position in property keyframes until the end of property keyframes
477 // is reached.
478 for (size_t i = 0; i < parsedKeyframes.size(); ++i)
479 parsedKeyframes[i].easing = easings[i];
480
481 // 12. If the “composite” member of the property-indexed keyframe is not an empty sequence:
482 if (document.settings().webAnimationsCompositeOperationsEnabled()) {
483 Vector<CompositeOperationOrAuto> compositeModes;
484 if (WTF::holds_alternative<Vector<CompositeOperationOrAuto>>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.composite))
485 compositeModes = WTF::get<Vector<CompositeOperationOrAuto>>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.composite);
486 else if (WTF::holds_alternative<CompositeOperationOrAuto>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.composite))
487 compositeModes.append(WTF::get<CompositeOperationOrAuto>(propertyIndexedKeyframe.baseProperties.composite));
488 if (!compositeModes.isEmpty()) {
489 // 1. Let composite modes be a sequence of CompositeOperationOrAuto values assigned from the “composite” member of property-indexed keyframe. If that member is a single
490 // CompositeOperationOrAuto value operation, let composite modes be a sequence of length one, with the value of the “composite” as its single item.
491 // 2. As with easings, if composite modes has fewer items than processed keyframes, repeat the elements in composite modes successively starting from the beginning of
492 // the list until composite modes has as many items as processed keyframes.
493 if (compositeModes.size() < parsedKeyframes.size()) {
494 size_t initialNumberOfCompositeModes = compositeModes.size();
495 for (i = initialNumberOfCompositeModes; i < parsedKeyframes.size(); ++i)
496 compositeModes.append(compositeModes[i % initialNumberOfCompositeModes]);
497 }
498 // 3. Assign each value in composite modes that is not auto to the keyframe-specific composite operation on the keyframe with the corresponding position in processed
499 // keyframes until the end of processed keyframes is reached.
500 for (size_t i = 0; i < compositeModes.size() && i < parsedKeyframes.size(); ++i) {
501 if (compositeModes[i] != CompositeOperationOrAuto::Auto)
502 parsedKeyframes[i].composite = compositeModes[i];
503 }
504 }
505 }
506
507 return { };
508}
509
510ExceptionOr<Ref<KeyframeEffect>> KeyframeEffect::create(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, Element* target, Strong<JSObject>&& keyframes, std::optional<Variant<double, KeyframeEffectOptions>>&& options)
511{
512 auto keyframeEffect = adoptRef(*new KeyframeEffect(target, PseudoId::None));
513
514 if (options) {
515 OptionalEffectTiming timing;
516 auto optionsValue = options.value();
517 if (WTF::holds_alternative<double>(optionsValue)) {
518 Variant<double, String> duration = WTF::get<double>(optionsValue);
519 timing.duration = duration;
520 } else {
521 auto keyframeEffectOptions = WTF::get<KeyframeEffectOptions>(optionsValue);
522
523 auto setPseudoElementResult = keyframeEffect->setPseudoElement(keyframeEffectOptions.pseudoElement);
524 if (setPseudoElementResult.hasException())
525 return setPseudoElementResult.releaseException();
526
527 timing = {
528 keyframeEffectOptions.duration,
529 keyframeEffectOptions.iterations,
530 keyframeEffectOptions.delay,
531 keyframeEffectOptions.endDelay,
532 keyframeEffectOptions.iterationStart,
533 keyframeEffectOptions.easing,
534 keyframeEffectOptions.fill,
535 keyframeEffectOptions.direction
536 };
537 }
538 auto updateTimingResult = keyframeEffect->updateTiming(timing);
539 if (updateTimingResult.hasException())
540 return updateTimingResult.releaseException();
541 }
542
543 auto processKeyframesResult = keyframeEffect->processKeyframes(lexicalGlobalObject, WTFMove(keyframes));
544 if (processKeyframesResult.hasException())
545 return processKeyframesResult.releaseException();
546
547 return keyframeEffect;
548}
549
550ExceptionOr<Ref<KeyframeEffect>> KeyframeEffect::create(JSC::JSGlobalObject&, Ref<KeyframeEffect>&& source)
551{
552 auto keyframeEffect = adoptRef(*new KeyframeEffect(nullptr, PseudoId::None));
553 keyframeEffect->copyPropertiesFromSource(WTFMove(source));
554 return keyframeEffect;
555}
556
557Ref<KeyframeEffect> KeyframeEffect::create(const Element& target, PseudoId pseudoId)
558{
559 return adoptRef(*new KeyframeEffect(const_cast<Element*>(&target), pseudoId));
560}
561
562KeyframeEffect::KeyframeEffect(Element* target, PseudoId pseudoId)
563 : m_target(target)
564 , m_pseudoId(pseudoId)
565{
566}
567
568void KeyframeEffect::copyPropertiesFromSource(Ref<KeyframeEffect>&& source)
569{
570 m_target = source->m_target;
571 m_pseudoId = source->m_pseudoId;
572 m_compositeOperation = source->m_compositeOperation;
573 m_iterationCompositeOperation = source->m_iterationCompositeOperation;
574
575 Vector<ParsedKeyframe> parsedKeyframes;
576 for (auto& sourceParsedKeyframe : source->m_parsedKeyframes) {
577 ParsedKeyframe parsedKeyframe;
578 parsedKeyframe.easing = sourceParsedKeyframe.easing;
579 parsedKeyframe.offset = sourceParsedKeyframe.offset;
580 parsedKeyframe.composite = sourceParsedKeyframe.composite;
581 parsedKeyframe.unparsedStyle = sourceParsedKeyframe.unparsedStyle;
582 parsedKeyframe.computedOffset = sourceParsedKeyframe.computedOffset;
583 parsedKeyframe.timingFunction = sourceParsedKeyframe.timingFunction;
584 parsedKeyframe.style = sourceParsedKeyframe.style->mutableCopy();
585 parsedKeyframes.append(WTFMove(parsedKeyframe));
586 }
587 m_parsedKeyframes = WTFMove(parsedKeyframes);
588
589 setFill(source->fill());
590 setDelay(source->delay());
591 setEndDelay(source->endDelay());
592 setDirection(source->direction());
593 setIterations(source->iterations());
594 setTimingFunction(source->timingFunction());
595 setIterationStart(source->iterationStart());
596 setIterationDuration(source->iterationDuration());
597 updateStaticTimingProperties();
598
599 KeyframeList keyframeList("keyframe-effect-" + createCanonicalUUIDString());
600 keyframeList.copyKeyframes(source->m_blendingKeyframes);
601 setBlendingKeyframes(keyframeList);
602}
603
604Vector<Strong<JSObject>> KeyframeEffect::getBindingsKeyframes(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject)
605{
606 if (is<DeclarativeAnimation>(animation()))
607 downcast<DeclarativeAnimation>(*animation()).flushPendingStyleChanges();
608 return getKeyframes(lexicalGlobalObject);
609}
610
611Vector<Strong<JSObject>> KeyframeEffect::getKeyframes(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject)
612{
613 // https://drafts.csswg.org/web-animations-1/#dom-keyframeeffectreadonly-getkeyframes
614
615 auto lock = JSLockHolder { &lexicalGlobalObject };
616
617 // Since keyframes are represented by a partially open-ended dictionary type that is not currently able to be expressed with WebIDL,
618 // the procedure used to prepare the result of this method is defined in prose below:
619 //
620 // 1. Let result be an empty sequence of objects.
621 Vector<Strong<JSObject>> result;
622
623 // 2. Let keyframes be the result of applying the procedure to compute missing keyframe offsets to the keyframes for this keyframe effect.
624
625 // 3. For each keyframe in keyframes perform the following steps:
626 if (m_parsedKeyframes.isEmpty() && m_blendingKeyframesSource != BlendingKeyframesSource::WebAnimation) {
627 auto* target = m_target.get();
628 auto* renderer = this->renderer();
629
630 auto computedStyleExtractor = ComputedStyleExtractor(target, false, m_pseudoId);
631
632 for (size_t i = 0; i < m_blendingKeyframes.size(); ++i) {
633 // 1. Initialize a dictionary object, output keyframe, using the following definition:
634 //
635 // dictionary BaseComputedKeyframe {
636 // double? offset = null;
637 // double computedOffset;
638 // DOMString easing = "linear";
639 // CompositeOperationOrAuto composite = "auto";
640 // };
641
642 auto& keyframe = m_blendingKeyframes[i];
643
644 // 2. Set offset, computedOffset, easing members of output keyframe to the respective values keyframe offset, computed keyframe offset,
645 // and keyframe-specific timing function of keyframe.
646 BaseComputedKeyframe computedKeyframe;
647 computedKeyframe.offset = keyframe.key();
648 computedKeyframe.computedOffset = keyframe.key();
649 // For CSS transitions, all keyframes should return "linear" since the effect's global timing function applies.
650 computedKeyframe.easing = is<CSSTransition>(animation()) ? "linear" : timingFunctionForKeyframeAtIndex(i)->cssText();
651
652 auto outputKeyframe = convertDictionaryToJS(lexicalGlobalObject, *jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(&lexicalGlobalObject), computedKeyframe);
653
654 // 3. For each animation property-value pair specified on keyframe, declaration, perform the following steps:
655 auto& style = *keyframe.style();
656 for (auto cssPropertyId : keyframe.properties()) {
657 if (cssPropertyId == CSSPropertyCustom)
658 continue;
659 // 1. Let property name be the result of applying the animation property name to IDL attribute name algorithm to the property name of declaration.
660 auto propertyName = CSSPropertyIDToIDLAttributeName(cssPropertyId);
661 // 2. Let IDL value be the result of serializing the property value of declaration by passing declaration to the algorithm to serialize a CSS value.
662 String idlValue = "";
663 if (auto cssValue = computedStyleExtractor.valueForPropertyInStyle(style, cssPropertyId, renderer))
664 idlValue = cssValue->cssText();
665 // 3. Let value be the result of converting IDL value to an ECMAScript String value.
666 auto value = toJS<IDLDOMString>(lexicalGlobalObject, idlValue);
667 // 4. Call the [[DefineOwnProperty]] internal method on output keyframe with property name property name,
668 // Property Descriptor { [[Writable]]: true, [[Enumerable]]: true, [[Configurable]]: true, [[Value]]: value } and Boolean flag false.
669 JSObject::defineOwnProperty(outputKeyframe, &lexicalGlobalObject, AtomString(propertyName).impl(), PropertyDescriptor(value, 0), false);
670 }
671
672 // 5. Append output keyframe to result.
673 result.append(JSC::Strong<JSC::JSObject> { lexicalGlobalObject.vm(), outputKeyframe });
674 }
675 } else {
676 for (size_t i = 0; i < m_parsedKeyframes.size(); ++i) {
677 // 1. Initialize a dictionary object, output keyframe, using the following definition:
678 //
679 // dictionary BaseComputedKeyframe {
680 // double? offset = null;
681 // double computedOffset;
682 // DOMString easing = "linear";
683 // CompositeOperationOrAuto composite = "auto";
684 // };
685
686 auto& parsedKeyframe = m_parsedKeyframes[i];
687
688 // 2. Set offset, computedOffset, easing, composite members of output keyframe to the respective values keyframe offset, computed keyframe
689 // offset, keyframe-specific timing function and keyframe-specific composite operation of keyframe.
690 BaseComputedKeyframe computedKeyframe;
691 computedKeyframe.offset = parsedKeyframe.offset;
692 computedKeyframe.computedOffset = parsedKeyframe.computedOffset;
693 computedKeyframe.easing = timingFunctionForKeyframeAtIndex(i)->cssText();
694
695 auto* scriptExecutionContext = jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(&lexicalGlobalObject)->scriptExecutionContext();
696 if (is<Document>(scriptExecutionContext)) {
697 if (downcast<Document>(*scriptExecutionContext).settings().webAnimationsCompositeOperationsEnabled())
698 computedKeyframe.composite = parsedKeyframe.composite;
699 }
700
701 auto outputKeyframe = convertDictionaryToJS(lexicalGlobalObject, *jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(&lexicalGlobalObject), computedKeyframe);
702
703 // 3. For each animation property-value pair specified on keyframe, declaration, perform the following steps:
704 for (auto it = parsedKeyframe.unparsedStyle.begin(), end = parsedKeyframe.unparsedStyle.end(); it != end; ++it) {
705 // 1. Let property name be the result of applying the animation property name to IDL attribute name algorithm to the property name of declaration.
706 auto propertyName = CSSPropertyIDToIDLAttributeName(it->key);
707 // 2. Let IDL value be the result of serializing the property value of declaration by passing declaration to the algorithm to serialize a CSS value.
708 // 3. Let value be the result of converting IDL value to an ECMAScript String value.
709 auto value = toJS<IDLDOMString>(lexicalGlobalObject, it->value);
710 // 4. Call the [[DefineOwnProperty]] internal method on output keyframe with property name property name,
711 // Property Descriptor { [[Writable]]: true, [[Enumerable]]: true, [[Configurable]]: true, [[Value]]: value } and Boolean flag false.
712 JSObject::defineOwnProperty(outputKeyframe, &lexicalGlobalObject, AtomString(propertyName).impl(), PropertyDescriptor(value, 0), false);
713 }
714
715 // 4. Append output keyframe to result.
716 result.append(JSC::Strong<JSC::JSObject> { lexicalGlobalObject.vm(), outputKeyframe });
717 }
718 }
719
720 // 4. Return result.
721 return result;
722}

724ExceptionOr<void> KeyframeEffect::setBindingsKeyframes(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, Strong<JSObject>&& keyframesInput)
725{
726 auto retVal = setKeyframes(lexicalGlobalObject, WTFMove(keyframesInput));
727 if (!retVal.hasException() && is<CSSAnimation>(animation()))
728 downcast<CSSAnimation>(*animation()).effectKeyframesWereSetUsingBindings();
729 return retVal;
730}
731
732ExceptionOr<void> KeyframeEffect::setKeyframes(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, Strong<JSObject>&& keyframesInput)
733{
734 auto processKeyframesResult = processKeyframes(lexicalGlobalObject, WTFMove(keyframesInput));
735 if (!processKeyframesResult.hasException() && animation())
736 animation()->effectTimingDidChange();
737 return processKeyframesResult;
738}
739
740ExceptionOr<void> KeyframeEffect::processKeyframes(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, Strong<JSObject>&& keyframesInput)
741{
742 // 1. If object is null, return an empty sequence of keyframes.
743 if (!keyframesInput.get())
744 return { };
745
746 VM& vm = lexicalGlobalObject.vm();
747 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
748
749 // 2. Let processed keyframes be an empty sequence of keyframes.
750 Vector<ParsedKeyframe> parsedKeyframes;
751
752 // 3. Let method be the result of GetMethod(object, @@iterator).
753 auto method = keyframesInput.get()->get(&lexicalGlobalObject, vm.propertyNames->iteratorSymbol);
754
755 // 4. Check the completion record of method.
756 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, Exception { TypeError });
757
758 // 5. Perform the steps corresponding to the first matching condition from below,
759 Vector<String> unusedEasings;
760 if (!method.isUndefined()) {
761 auto retVal = processIterableKeyframes(lexicalGlobalObject, WTFMove(keyframesInput), WTFMove(method), parsedKeyframes);
762 if (retVal.hasException())
763 return retVal.releaseException();
764 } else {
765 auto retVal = processPropertyIndexedKeyframes(lexicalGlobalObject, WTFMove(keyframesInput), parsedKeyframes, unusedEasings);
766 if (retVal.hasException())
767 return retVal.releaseException();
768 }
769
770 // 6. If processed keyframes is not loosely sorted by offset, throw a TypeError and abort these steps.
771 // 7. If there exist any keyframe in processed keyframes whose keyframe offset is non-null and less than
772 // zero or greater than one, throw a TypeError and abort these steps.
773 double lastNonNullOffset = -1;
774 for (auto& keyframe : parsedKeyframes) {
775 if (!keyframe.offset)
776 continue;
777 auto offset = keyframe.offset.value();
778 if (offset < lastNonNullOffset || offset < 0 || offset > 1)
779 return Exception { TypeError };
780 lastNonNullOffset = offset;
781 }
782
783 // We take a slight detour from the spec text and compute the missing keyframe offsets right away
784 // since they can be computed up-front.
785 computeMissingKeyframeOffsets(parsedKeyframes);
786
787 // 8. For each frame in processed keyframes, perform the following steps:
788 for (auto& keyframe : parsedKeyframes) {
789 // Let the timing function of frame be the result of parsing the “easing” property on frame using the CSS syntax
790 // defined for the easing property of the AnimationEffectTiming interface.
791 // If parsing the “easing” property fails, throw a TypeError and abort this procedure.
792 auto timingFunctionResult = TimingFunction::createFromCSSText(keyframe.easing);
793 if (timingFunctionResult.hasException())
794 return timingFunctionResult.releaseException();
795 keyframe.timingFunction = timingFunctionResult.returnValue();
796 }
797
798 // 9. Parse each of the values in unused easings using the CSS syntax defined for easing property of the
799 // AnimationEffectTiming interface, and if any of the values fail to parse, throw a TypeError
800 // and abort this procedure.
801 for (auto& easing : unusedEasings) {
802 auto timingFunctionResult = TimingFunction::createFromCSSText(easing);
803 if (timingFunctionResult.hasException())
804 return timingFunctionResult.releaseException();
805 }
806
807 m_parsedKeyframes = WTFMove(parsedKeyframes);
808
809 clearBlendingKeyframes();
810
811 return { };
812}
813
814void KeyframeEffect::updateBlendingKeyframes(RenderStyle& elementStyle, const RenderStyle* parentElementStyle)
815{
816 if (!m_blendingKeyframes.isEmpty() || !m_target)
817 return;
818
819 KeyframeList keyframeList("keyframe-effect-" + createCanonicalUUIDString());
820 auto& styleResolver = m_target->styleResolver();
821
822 for (auto& keyframe : m_parsedKeyframes) {
823 KeyframeValue keyframeValue(keyframe.computedOffset, nullptr);
824 keyframeValue.setTimingFunction(keyframe.timingFunction->clone());
825
826 auto styleProperties = keyframe.style->immutableCopyIfNeeded();
827 for (unsigned i = 0; i < styleProperties->propertyCount(); ++i)
828 keyframeList.addProperty(styleProperties->propertyAt(i).id());
829
830 auto keyframeRule = StyleRuleKeyframe::create(WTFMove(styleProperties));
831 keyframeValue.setStyle(styleResolver.styleForKeyframe(*m_target, &elementStyle, parentElementStyle, keyframeRule.ptr(), keyframeValue));
832 keyframeList.insert(WTFMove(keyframeValue));
833 }
834
835 setBlendingKeyframes(keyframeList);
836}
837
838const HashSet<CSSPropertyID>& KeyframeEffect::animatedProperties()
839{
840 if (!m_blendingKeyframes.isEmpty())
841 return m_blendingKeyframes.properties();
842
843 if (m_animatedProperties.isEmpty()) {
844 for (auto& keyframe : m_parsedKeyframes) {
845 for (auto keyframeProperty : keyframe.unparsedStyle.keys())
846 m_animatedProperties.add(keyframeProperty);
847 }
848 }
849
850 return m_animatedProperties;
851}
852
853bool KeyframeEffect::animatesProperty(CSSPropertyID property) const
854{
855 if (!m_blendingKeyframes.isEmpty())
856 return m_blendingKeyframes.properties().contains(property);
857
858 for (auto& keyframe : m_parsedKeyframes) {
859 for (auto keyframeProperty : keyframe.unparsedStyle.keys()) {
860 if (keyframeProperty == property)
861 return true;
862 }
863 }
864 return false;
865}
866
867bool KeyframeEffect::forceLayoutIfNeeded()
868{
869 if (!m_needsForcedLayout || !m_target)
870 return false;
871
872 auto* renderer = this->renderer();
873 if (!renderer || !renderer->parent())
874 return false;
875
876 ASSERT(document());
877 auto* frameView = document()->view();
878 if (!frameView)
879 return false;
880
881 frameView->forceLayout();
882 return true;
883}
