886void KeyframeEffect::clearBlendingKeyframes()
887{
888 m_blendingKeyframesSource = BlendingKeyframesSource::WebAnimation;
889 m_blendingKeyframes.clear();
890}
891
892void KeyframeEffect::setBlendingKeyframes(KeyframeList& blendingKeyframes)
893{
894 m_blendingKeyframes = WTFMove(blendingKeyframes);
895 m_animatedProperties.clear();
896
897 computedNeedsForcedLayout();
898 computeStackingContextImpact();
899 computeAcceleratedPropertiesState();
900 computeSomeKeyframesUseStepsTimingFunction();
901
902 checkForMatchingTransformFunctionLists();
903 checkForMatchingFilterFunctionLists();
904#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
905 checkForMatchingBackdropFilterFunctionLists();
906#endif
907 checkForMatchingColorFilterFunctionLists();
908}
909
910void KeyframeEffect::checkForMatchingTransformFunctionLists()
911{
912 m_transformFunctionListsMatch = false;
913
914 if (m_blendingKeyframes.size() < 2 || !m_blendingKeyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyTransform))
915 return;
916
917 // Empty transforms match anything, so find the first non-empty entry as the reference.
918 size_t numKeyframes = m_blendingKeyframes.size();
919 size_t firstNonEmptyTransformKeyframeIndex = numKeyframes;
920
921 for (size_t i = 0; i < numKeyframes; ++i) {
922 const KeyframeValue& currentKeyframe = m_blendingKeyframes[i];
923 if (currentKeyframe.style()->transform().operations().size()) {
924 firstNonEmptyTransformKeyframeIndex = i;
925 break;
926 }
927 }
928
929 if (firstNonEmptyTransformKeyframeIndex == numKeyframes)
930 return;
931
932 const TransformOperations* firstVal = &m_blendingKeyframes[firstNonEmptyTransformKeyframeIndex].style()->transform();
933 for (size_t i = firstNonEmptyTransformKeyframeIndex + 1; i < numKeyframes; ++i) {
934 const KeyframeValue& currentKeyframe = m_blendingKeyframes[i];
935 const TransformOperations* val = &currentKeyframe.style()->transform();
936
937 // An empty transform list matches anything.
938 if (val->operations().isEmpty())
939 continue;
940
941 if (!firstVal->operationsMatch(*val))
942 return;
943 }
944
945 m_transformFunctionListsMatch = true;
946}
947
948bool KeyframeEffect::checkForMatchingFilterFunctionLists(CSSPropertyID propertyID, const std::function<const FilterOperations& (const RenderStyle&)>& filtersGetter) const
949{
950 if (m_blendingKeyframes.size() < 2 || !m_blendingKeyframes.containsProperty(propertyID))
951 return false;
952
953 // Empty filters match anything, so find the first non-empty entry as the reference.
954 size_t numKeyframes = m_blendingKeyframes.size();
955 size_t firstNonEmptyKeyframeIndex = numKeyframes;
956
957 for (size_t i = 0; i < numKeyframes; ++i) {
958 if (filtersGetter(*m_blendingKeyframes[i].style()).operations().size()) {
959 firstNonEmptyKeyframeIndex = i;
960 break;
961 }
962 }
963
964 if (firstNonEmptyKeyframeIndex == numKeyframes)
965 return false;
966
967 auto& firstVal = filtersGetter(*m_blendingKeyframes[firstNonEmptyKeyframeIndex].style());
968 for (size_t i = firstNonEmptyKeyframeIndex + 1; i < numKeyframes; ++i) {
969 auto& value = filtersGetter(*m_blendingKeyframes[i].style());
970
971 // An empty filter list matches anything.
972 if (value.operations().isEmpty())
973 continue;
974
975 if (!firstVal.operationsMatch(value))
976 return false;
977 }
978
979 return true;
980}
981
982void KeyframeEffect::checkForMatchingFilterFunctionLists()
983{
984 m_filterFunctionListsMatch = checkForMatchingFilterFunctionLists(CSSPropertyFilter, [] (const RenderStyle& style) -> const FilterOperations& {
985 return style.filter();
986 });
987}
988
989#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
990void KeyframeEffect::checkForMatchingBackdropFilterFunctionLists()
991{
992 m_backdropFilterFunctionListsMatch = checkForMatchingFilterFunctionLists(CSSPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter, [] (const RenderStyle& style) -> const FilterOperations& {
993 return style.backdropFilter();
994 });
995}
996#endif
997
998void KeyframeEffect::checkForMatchingColorFilterFunctionLists()
999{
1000 m_colorFilterFunctionListsMatch = checkForMatchingFilterFunctionLists(CSSPropertyAppleColorFilter, [] (const RenderStyle& style) -> const FilterOperations& {
1001 return style.appleColorFilter();
1002 });
1003}
1004
1005void KeyframeEffect::computeDeclarativeAnimationBlendingKeyframes(const RenderStyle* oldStyle, const RenderStyle& newStyle, const RenderStyle* parentElementStyle)
1006{
1007 ASSERT(is<DeclarativeAnimation>(animation()));
1008 if (is<CSSAnimation>(animation()))
1009 computeCSSAnimationBlendingKeyframes(newStyle, parentElementStyle);
1010 else if (is<CSSTransition>(animation()))
1011 computeCSSTransitionBlendingKeyframes(oldStyle, newStyle);
1012}
1013
1014void KeyframeEffect::computeCSSAnimationBlendingKeyframes(const RenderStyle& unanimatedStyle, const RenderStyle* parentElementStyle)
1015{
1016 ASSERT(is<CSSAnimation>(animation()));
1017 ASSERT(document());
1018
1019 auto cssAnimation = downcast<CSSAnimation>(animation());
1020 auto& backingAnimation = cssAnimation->backingAnimation();
1021
1022 KeyframeList keyframeList(backingAnimation.name().string);
1023 if (auto* styleScope = Style::Scope::forOrdinal(*m_target, backingAnimation.nameStyleScopeOrdinal()))
1024 styleScope->resolver().keyframeStylesForAnimation(*m_target, &unanimatedStyle, parentElementStyle, keyframeList);
1025
1026 // Ensure resource loads for all the frames.
1027 for (auto& keyframe : keyframeList.keyframes()) {
1028 if (auto* style = const_cast<RenderStyle*>(keyframe.style()))
1029 Style::loadPendingResources(*style, *document(), m_target.get());
1030 }
1031
1032 m_blendingKeyframesSource = BlendingKeyframesSource::CSSAnimation;
1033 setBlendingKeyframes(keyframeList);
1034}
1035
1036void KeyframeEffect::computeCSSTransitionBlendingKeyframes(const RenderStyle* oldStyle, const RenderStyle& newStyle)
1037{
1038 ASSERT(is<CSSTransition>(animation()));
1039 ASSERT(document());
1040
1041 if (!oldStyle || m_blendingKeyframes.size())
1042 return;
1043
1044 auto property = downcast<CSSTransition>(animation())->property();
1045
1046 auto toStyle = RenderStyle::clonePtr(newStyle);
1047 if (m_target)
1048 Style::loadPendingResources(*toStyle, *document(), m_target.get());
1049
1050 KeyframeList keyframeList("keyframe-effect-" + createCanonicalUUIDString());
1051 keyframeList.addProperty(property);
1052
1053 KeyframeValue fromKeyframeValue(0, RenderStyle::clonePtr(*oldStyle));
1054 fromKeyframeValue.addProperty(property);
1055 keyframeList.insert(WTFMove(fromKeyframeValue));
1056
1057 KeyframeValue toKeyframeValue(1, WTFMove(toStyle));
1058 toKeyframeValue.addProperty(property);
1059 keyframeList.insert(WTFMove(toKeyframeValue));
1060
1061 m_blendingKeyframesSource = BlendingKeyframesSource::CSSTransition;
1062 setBlendingKeyframes(keyframeList);
1063}
1064
1065void KeyframeEffect::computedNeedsForcedLayout()
1066{
1067 m_needsForcedLayout = false;
1068 if (is<CSSTransition>(animation()) || !m_blendingKeyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyTransform))
1069 return;
1070
1071 size_t numberOfKeyframes = m_blendingKeyframes.size();
1072 for (size_t i = 0; i < numberOfKeyframes; i++) {
1073 auto* keyframeStyle = m_blendingKeyframes[i].style();
1074 if (!keyframeStyle) {
1075 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1076 continue;
1077 }
1078 if (keyframeStyle->hasTransform()) {
1079 auto& transformOperations = keyframeStyle->transform();
1080 for (const auto& operation : transformOperations.operations()) {
1081 if (operation->isTranslateTransformOperationType()) {
1082 auto translation = downcast<TranslateTransformOperation>(operation.get());
1083 if (translation->x().isPercent() || translation->y().isPercent()) {
1084 m_needsForcedLayout = true;
1085 return;
1086 }
1087 }
1088 }
1089 }
1090 }
1091}
1092
1093void KeyframeEffect::computeStackingContextImpact()
1094{
1095 m_triggersStackingContext = false;
1096 for (auto cssPropertyId : m_blendingKeyframes.properties()) {
1097 if (WillChangeData::propertyCreatesStackingContext(cssPropertyId)) {
1098 m_triggersStackingContext = true;
1099 break;
1100 }
1101 }
1102}
1103
1104void KeyframeEffect::animationTimelineDidChange(AnimationTimeline* timeline)
1105{
1106 auto target = targetStyleable();
1107 if (!target)
1108 return;
1109
1110 if (timeline)
1111 m_inTargetEffectStack = target->ensureKeyframeEffectStack().addEffect(*this);
1112 else {
1113 target->ensureKeyframeEffectStack().removeEffect(*this);
1114 m_inTargetEffectStack = false;
1115 }
1116}
1117
1118void KeyframeEffect::animationTimingDidChange()
1119{
1120 updateEffectStackMembership();
1121}
1122
1123void KeyframeEffect::updateEffectStackMembership()
1124{
1125 auto target = targetStyleable();
1126 if (!target)
1127 return;
1128
1129 bool isRelevant = animation() && animation()->isRelevant();
1130 if (isRelevant && !m_inTargetEffectStack)
1131 m_inTargetEffectStack = target->ensureKeyframeEffectStack().addEffect(*this);
1132 else if (!isRelevant && m_inTargetEffectStack) {
1133 target->ensureKeyframeEffectStack().removeEffect(*this);
1134 m_inTargetEffectStack = false;
1135 }
1136}
1137
1138void KeyframeEffect::setAnimation(WebAnimation* animation)
1139{
1140 bool animationChanged = animation != this->animation();
1141 AnimationEffect::setAnimation(animation);
1142
1143 if (!animationChanged)
1144 return;
1145
1146 if (animation)
1147 animation->updateRelevance();
1148 updateEffectStackMembership();
1149}
1150
1151const std::optional<const Styleable> KeyframeEffect::targetStyleable() const
1152{
1153 if (m_target)
1154 return Styleable(*m_target, m_pseudoId);
1155 return std::nullopt;
1156}
1157
1158bool KeyframeEffect::targetsPseudoElement() const
1159{
1160 return m_target.get() && m_pseudoId != PseudoId::None;
1161}
1162
1163Element* KeyframeEffect::targetElementOrPseudoElement() const
1164{
1165 if (m_target) {
1166 if (m_pseudoId == PseudoId::Before)
1167 return m_target->beforePseudoElement();
1168
1169 if (m_pseudoId == PseudoId::After)
1170 return m_target->afterPseudoElement();
1171 }
1172
1173 return m_target.get();
1174}
1175
1176void KeyframeEffect::setTarget(RefPtr<Element>&& newTarget)
1177{
1178 if (m_target == newTarget)
1179 return;
1180
1181 auto& previousTargetStyleable = targetStyleable();
1182 RefPtr<Element> protector;
1183 if (previousTargetStyleable)
1184 protector = makeRefPtr(previousTargetStyleable->element);
1185 m_target = WTFMove(newTarget);
1186 didChangeTargetStyleable(previousTargetStyleable);
1187}
1188
1189const String KeyframeEffect::pseudoElement() const
1190{
1191 // https://drafts.csswg.org/web-animations/#dom-keyframeeffect-pseudoelement
1192
1193 // The target pseudo-selector. null if this effect has no effect target or if the effect target is an element (i.e. not a pseudo-element).
1194 // When the effect target is a pseudo-element, this specifies the pseudo-element selector (e.g. ::before).
1195 if (targetsPseudoElement())
1196 return pseudoIdAsString(m_pseudoId);
1197 return { };
1198}
1199
1200ExceptionOr<void> KeyframeEffect::setPseudoElement(const String& pseudoElement)
1201{
1202 // https://drafts.csswg.org/web-animations/#dom-keyframeeffect-pseudoelement
1203
1204 // On setting, sets the target pseudo-selector of the animation effect to the provided value after applying the following exceptions:
1205 //
1206 // - If the provided value is not null and is an invalid <pseudo-element-selector>, the user agent must throw a DOMException with error
1207 // name SyntaxError and leave the target pseudo-selector of this animation effect unchanged. Note, that invalid in this context follows
1208 // the definition of an invalid selector defined in [SELECTORS-4] such that syntactically invalid pseudo-elements as well as pseudo-elements
1209 // for which the user agent has no usable level of support are both deemed invalid.
1210 // - If one of the legacy Selectors Level 2 single-colon selectors (':before', ':after', ':first-letter', or ':first-line') is specified,
1211 // the target pseudo-selector must be set to the equivalent two-colon selector (e.g. '::before').
1212 auto pseudoId = PseudoId::None;
1213 if (!pseudoElement.isNull()) {
1214 auto isLegacy = pseudoElement == ":before" || pseudoElement == ":after" || pseudoElement == ":first-letter" || pseudoElement == ":first-line";
1215 if (!isLegacy && !pseudoElement.startsWith("::"))
1216 return Exception { SyntaxError };
1217 auto pseudoType = CSSSelector::parsePseudoElementType(pseudoElement.substring(isLegacy ? 1 : 2));
1218 if (pseudoType == CSSSelector::PseudoElementUnknown)
1219 return Exception { SyntaxError };
1220 pseudoId = CSSSelector::pseudoId(pseudoType);
1221 }
1222
1223 if (pseudoId == m_pseudoId)
1224 return { };
1225
1226 auto& previousTargetStyleable = targetStyleable();
1227 m_pseudoId = pseudoId;
1228 didChangeTargetStyleable(previousTargetStyleable);
1229
1230 return { };
1231}
1232
1233void KeyframeEffect::didChangeTargetStyleable(const std::optional<const Styleable>& previousTargetStyleable)
1234{
1235 auto newTargetStyleable = targetStyleable();
1236
1237 // We must ensure a PseudoElement exists for this m_target / m_pseudoId pair if both are specified.
1238 // FIXME: Ideally this wouldn't be necessary.
1239 auto* newTargetElementOrPseudoElement = elementOrPseudoElementForStyleable(newTargetStyleable);
1240 if (!newTargetElementOrPseudoElement && m_target.get() && m_pseudoId != PseudoId::None) {
1241 // FIXME: We only support targeting ::before and ::after pseudo-elements at the moment.
1242 if (m_pseudoId == PseudoId::Before || m_pseudoId == PseudoId::After)
1243 newTargetElementOrPseudoElement = &m_target->ensurePseudoElement(m_pseudoId);
1244 }
1245
1246 if (auto* effectAnimation = animation())
1247 effectAnimation->effectTargetDidChange(previousTargetStyleable, newTargetStyleable);
1248
1249 clearBlendingKeyframes();
1250
1251 // We need to invalidate the effect now that the target has changed
1252 // to ensure the effect's styles are applied to the new target right away.
1253 invalidate();
1254
1255 // Likewise, we need to invalidate styles on the previous target so that
1256 // any animated styles are removed immediately.
1257 invalidateElement(previousTargetStyleable);
1258
1259 if (previousTargetStyleable) {
1260 previousTargetStyleable->ensureKeyframeEffectStack().removeEffect(*this);
1261 m_inTargetEffectStack = false;
1262 }
1263
1264 if (newTargetStyleable)
1265 m_inTargetEffectStack = newTargetStyleable->ensureKeyframeEffectStack().addEffect(*this);
1266}
1267
1268void KeyframeEffect::apply(RenderStyle& targetStyle, const RenderStyle* parentElementStyle, std::optional<Seconds> startTime)
1269{
1270 if (!m_target)
1271 return;
1272
1273 updateBlendingKeyframes(targetStyle, parentElementStyle);
1274
1275 auto computedTiming = getComputedTiming(startTime);
1276 if (!startTime) {
1277 m_phaseAtLastApplication = computedTiming.phase;
1278 if (auto* target = targetElementOrPseudoElement())
1279 InspectorInstrumentation::willApplyKeyframeEffect(*target, *this, computedTiming);
1280 }
1281
1282 if (!computedTiming.progress)
1283 return;
1284
1285 setAnimatedPropertiesInStyle(targetStyle, computedTiming.progress.value());
1286}
1287
1288bool KeyframeEffect::isCurrentlyAffectingProperty(CSSPropertyID property, Accelerated accelerated) const
1289{
1290 if (accelerated == Accelerated::Yes && !isRunningAccelerated() && !isAboutToRunAccelerated())
1291 return false;
1292
1293 if (!m_blendingKeyframes.properties().contains(property))
1294 return false;
1295
1296 return m_phaseAtLastApplication == AnimationEffectPhase::Active;
1297}
1298
1299bool KeyframeEffect::isRunningAcceleratedAnimationForProperty(CSSPropertyID property) const
1300{
1301 return isRunningAccelerated() && CSSPropertyAnimation::animationOfPropertyIsAccelerated(property) && m_blendingKeyframes.properties().contains(property);
1302}
1303
1304bool KeyframeEffect::isTargetingTransformRelatedProperty() const
1305{
1306 return m_blendingKeyframes.properties().contains(CSSPropertyTranslate)
1307 || m_blendingKeyframes.properties().contains(CSSPropertyScale)
1308 || m_blendingKeyframes.properties().contains(CSSPropertyRotate)
1309 || m_blendingKeyframes.properties().contains(CSSPropertyTransform);
1310}
1311
1312bool KeyframeEffect::isRunningAcceleratedTransformRelatedAnimation() const
1313{
1314 return isRunningAccelerated() && isTargetingTransformRelatedProperty();
1315}
1316
1317void KeyframeEffect::invalidate()
1318{
1319 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Animations, stream << "KeyframeEffect::invalidate on element " << ValueOrNull(targetElementOrPseudoElement()));
1320 invalidateElement(targetStyleable());
1321}
1322
1323void KeyframeEffect::computeAcceleratedPropertiesState()
1324{
1325 bool hasSomeAcceleratedProperties = false;
1326 bool hasSomeUnacceleratedProperties = false;
1327
1328 for (auto cssPropertyId : m_blendingKeyframes.properties()) {
1329 // If any animated property can be accelerated, then the animation should run accelerated.
1330 if (CSSPropertyAnimation::animationOfPropertyIsAccelerated(cssPropertyId))
1331 hasSomeAcceleratedProperties = true;
1332 else
1333 hasSomeUnacceleratedProperties = true;
1334 if (hasSomeAcceleratedProperties && hasSomeUnacceleratedProperties)
1335 break;
1336 }
1337
1338 if (!hasSomeAcceleratedProperties)
1339 m_acceleratedPropertiesState = AcceleratedProperties::None;
1340 else if (hasSomeUnacceleratedProperties)
1341 m_acceleratedPropertiesState = AcceleratedProperties::Some;
1342 else
1343 m_acceleratedPropertiesState = AcceleratedProperties::All;
1344}
1345
1346void KeyframeEffect::computeSomeKeyframesUseStepsTimingFunction()
1347{
1348 m_someKeyframesUseStepsTimingFunction = false;
1349
1350 size_t numberOfKeyframes = m_blendingKeyframes.size();
1351
1352 // If we're dealing with a CSS Animation and it specifies a default steps() timing function,
1353 // we need to check that any of the specified keyframes either does not have an explicit timing
1354 // function or specifies an explicit steps() timing function.
1355 if (is<CSSAnimation>(animation()) && is<StepsTimingFunction>(downcast<DeclarativeAnimation>(*animation()).backingAnimation().timingFunction())) {
1356 for (size_t i = 0; i < numberOfKeyframes; i++) {
1357 auto* timingFunction = m_blendingKeyframes[i].timingFunction();
1358 if (!timingFunction || is<StepsTimingFunction>(timingFunction)) {
1359 m_someKeyframesUseStepsTimingFunction = true;
1360 return;
1361 }
1362 }
1363 return;
1364 }
1365
1366 // For any other type of animation, we just need to check whether any of the keyframes specify
1367 // an explicit steps() timing function.
1368 for (size_t i = 0; i < numberOfKeyframes; i++) {
1369 if (is<StepsTimingFunction>(m_blendingKeyframes[i].timingFunction())) {
1370 m_someKeyframesUseStepsTimingFunction = true;
1371 return;
1372 }
1373 }
1374}
1375
1376bool KeyframeEffect::hasImplicitKeyframes() const
1377{
1378 auto numberOfKeyframes = m_parsedKeyframes.size();
1379
1380 // If we have no keyframes, then there cannot be any implicit keyframes.
1381 if (!numberOfKeyframes)
1382 return false;
1383
1384 // If we have a single keyframe, then there has to be at least one implicit keyframe.
1385 if (numberOfKeyframes == 1)
1386 return true;
1387
1388 // If we have two or more keyframes, then we have implicit keyframes if the first and last
1389 // keyframes don't have 0 and 1 respectively as their computed offset.
1390 return m_parsedKeyframes[0].computedOffset || m_parsedKeyframes[numberOfKeyframes - 1].computedOffset != 1;
1391}
1392
1393void KeyframeEffect::getAnimatedStyle(std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle>& animatedStyle)
1394{
1395 if (!renderer() || !animation())
1396 return;
1397
1398 auto progress = getComputedTiming().progress;
1399 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Animations, stream << "KeyframeEffect " << this << " getAnimatedStyle - progress " << progress);
1400 if (!progress)
1401 return;
1402
1403 if (!animatedStyle) {
1404 if (auto* style = targetStyleable()->lastStyleChangeEventStyle())
1405 animatedStyle = RenderStyle::clonePtr(*style);
1406 else
1407 animatedStyle = RenderStyle::clonePtr(renderer()->style());
1408 }
1409
1410 setAnimatedPropertiesInStyle(*animatedStyle.get(), progress.value());
1411}
1412
1413void KeyframeEffect::setAnimatedPropertiesInStyle(RenderStyle& targetStyle, double iterationProgress)
1414{
1415 auto& properties = m_blendingKeyframes.properties();
1416
1417 // In the case of CSS Transitions we already know that there are only two keyframes, one where offset=0 and one where offset=1,
1418 // and only a single CSS property so we can simply blend based on the style available on those keyframes with the provided iteration
1419 // progress which already accounts for the transition's timing function.
1420 if (m_blendingKeyframesSource == BlendingKeyframesSource::CSSTransition) {
1421 ASSERT(properties.size() == 1);
1422 CSSPropertyAnimation::blendProperties(this, *properties.begin(), targetStyle, *m_blendingKeyframes[0].style(), *m_blendingKeyframes[1].style(), iterationProgress);
1423 return;
1424 }
1425
1426 // 4.4.3. The effect value of a keyframe effect
1427 // https://drafts.csswg.org/web-animations-1/#the-effect-value-of-a-keyframe-animation-effect
1428 //
1429 // The effect value of a single property referenced by a keyframe effect as one of its target properties,
1430 // for a given iteration progress, current iteration and underlying value is calculated as follows.
1431
1432 updateBlendingKeyframes(targetStyle, nullptr);
1433 if (m_blendingKeyframes.isEmpty())
1434 return;
1435
1436 for (auto cssPropertyId : properties) {
1437 // 1. If iteration progress is unresolved abort this procedure.
1438 // 2. Let target property be the longhand property for which the effect value is to be calculated.
1439 // 3. If animation type of the target property is not animatable abort this procedure since the effect cannot be applied.
1440 // 4. Define the neutral value for composition as a value which, when combined with an underlying value using the add composite operation,
1441 // produces the underlying value.
1442
1443 // 5. Let property-specific keyframes be the result of getting the set of computed keyframes for this keyframe effect.
1444 // 6. Remove any keyframes from property-specific keyframes that do not have a property value for target property.
1445 unsigned numberOfKeyframesWithZeroOffset = 0;
1446 unsigned numberOfKeyframesWithOneOffset = 0;
1447 Vector<std::optional<size_t>> propertySpecificKeyframes;
1448 for (size_t i = 0; i < m_blendingKeyframes.size(); ++i) {
1449 auto& keyframe = m_blendingKeyframes[i];
1450 auto offset = keyframe.key();
1451 if (!keyframe.containsProperty(cssPropertyId)) {
1452 // If we're dealing with a CSS animation, we consider the first and last keyframes to always have the property listed
1453 // since the underlying style was provided and should be captured.
1454 if (m_blendingKeyframesSource == BlendingKeyframesSource::WebAnimation || (offset && offset < 1))
1455 continue;
1456 }
1457 if (!offset)
1458 numberOfKeyframesWithZeroOffset++;
1459 if (offset == 1)
1460 numberOfKeyframesWithOneOffset++;
1461 propertySpecificKeyframes.append(i);
1462 }
1463
1464 // 7. If property-specific keyframes is empty, return underlying value.
1465 if (propertySpecificKeyframes.isEmpty())
1466 continue;
1467
1468 // 8. If there is no keyframe in property-specific keyframes with a computed keyframe offset of 0, create a new keyframe with a computed keyframe
1469 // offset of 0, a property value set to the neutral value for composition, and a composite operation of add, and prepend it to the beginning of
1470 // property-specific keyframes.
1471 if (!numberOfKeyframesWithZeroOffset) {
1472 propertySpecificKeyframes.insert(0, std::nullopt);
1473 numberOfKeyframesWithZeroOffset = 1;
1474 }
1475
1476 // 9. Similarly, if there is no keyframe in property-specific keyframes with a computed keyframe offset of 1, create a new keyframe with a computed
1477 // keyframe offset of 1, a property value set to the neutral value for composition, and a composite operation of add, and append it to the end of
1478 // property-specific keyframes.
1479 if (!numberOfKeyframesWithOneOffset) {
1480 propertySpecificKeyframes.append(std::nullopt);
1481 numberOfKeyframesWithOneOffset = 1;
1482 }
1483
1484 // 10. Let interval endpoints be an empty sequence of keyframes.
1485 Vector<std::optional<size_t>> intervalEndpoints;
1486
1487 // 11. Populate interval endpoints by following the steps from the first matching condition from below:
1488 if (iterationProgress < 0 && numberOfKeyframesWithZeroOffset > 1) {
1489 // If iteration progress < 0 and there is more than one keyframe in property-specific keyframes with a computed keyframe offset of 0,
1490 // Add the first keyframe in property-specific keyframes to interval endpoints.
1491 intervalEndpoints.append(propertySpecificKeyframes.first());
1492 } else if (iterationProgress >= 1 && numberOfKeyframesWithOneOffset > 1) {
1493 // If iteration progress ≥ 1 and there is more than one keyframe in property-specific keyframes with a computed keyframe offset of 1,
1494 // Add the last keyframe in property-specific keyframes to interval endpoints.
1495 intervalEndpoints.append(propertySpecificKeyframes.last());
1496 } else {
1497 // Otherwise,
1498 // 1. Append to interval endpoints the last keyframe in property-specific keyframes whose computed keyframe offset is less than or equal
1499 // to iteration progress and less than 1. If there is no such keyframe (because, for example, the iteration progress is negative),
1500 // add the last keyframe whose computed keyframe offset is 0.
1501 // 2. Append to interval endpoints the next keyframe in property-specific keyframes after the one added in the previous step.
1502 size_t indexOfLastKeyframeWithZeroOffset = 0;
1503 int indexOfFirstKeyframeToAddToIntervalEndpoints = -1;
1504 for (size_t i = 0; i < propertySpecificKeyframes.size(); ++i) {
1505 auto keyframeIndex = propertySpecificKeyframes[i];
1506 auto offset = [&] () -> double {
1507 if (!keyframeIndex)
1508 return i ? 1 : 0;
1509 return m_blendingKeyframes[keyframeIndex.value()].key();
1510 }();
1511 if (!offset)
1512 indexOfLastKeyframeWithZeroOffset = i;
1513 if (offset <= iterationProgress && offset < 1)
1514 indexOfFirstKeyframeToAddToIntervalEndpoints = i;
1515 else
1516 break;
1517 }
1518
1519 if (indexOfFirstKeyframeToAddToIntervalEndpoints >= 0) {
1520 intervalEndpoints.append(propertySpecificKeyframes[indexOfFirstKeyframeToAddToIntervalEndpoints]);
1521 intervalEndpoints.append(propertySpecificKeyframes[indexOfFirstKeyframeToAddToIntervalEndpoints + 1]);
1522 } else {
1523 ASSERT(indexOfLastKeyframeWithZeroOffset < propertySpecificKeyframes.size() - 1);
1524 intervalEndpoints.append(propertySpecificKeyframes[indexOfLastKeyframeWithZeroOffset]);
1525 intervalEndpoints.append(propertySpecificKeyframes[indexOfLastKeyframeWithZeroOffset + 1]);
1526 }
1527 }
1528
1529 // 12. For each keyframe in interval endpoints…
1530 // FIXME: we don't support this step yet since we don't deal with any composite operation other than "replace".
1531
1532 // 13. If there is only one keyframe in interval endpoints return the property value of target property on that keyframe.
1533 if (intervalEndpoints.size() == 1) {
1534 auto keyframeIndex = intervalEndpoints[0];
1535 auto keyframeStyle = !keyframeIndex ? &targetStyle : m_blendingKeyframes[keyframeIndex.value()].style();
1536 CSSPropertyAnimation::blendProperties(this, cssPropertyId, targetStyle, *keyframeStyle, *keyframeStyle, 0);
1537 continue;
1538 }
1539
1540 // 14. Let start offset be the computed keyframe offset of the first keyframe in interval endpoints.
1541 auto startKeyframeIndex = intervalEndpoints.first();
1542 auto startOffset = !startKeyframeIndex ? 0 : m_blendingKeyframes[startKeyframeIndex.value()].key();
1543
1544 // 15. Let end offset be the computed keyframe offset of last keyframe in interval endpoints.
1545 auto endKeyframeIndex = intervalEndpoints.last();
1546 auto endOffset = !endKeyframeIndex ? 1 : m_blendingKeyframes[endKeyframeIndex.value()].key();
1547
1548 // 16. Let interval distance be the result of evaluating (iteration progress - start offset) / (end offset - start offset).
1549 auto intervalDistance = (iterationProgress - startOffset) / (endOffset - startOffset);
1550
1551 // 17. Let transformed distance be the result of evaluating the timing function associated with the first keyframe in interval endpoints
1552 // passing interval distance as the input progress.
1553 auto transformedDistance = intervalDistance;
1554 if (startKeyframeIndex) {
1555 if (auto duration = iterationDuration()) {
1556 auto rangeDuration = (endOffset - startOffset) * duration.seconds();
1557 if (auto* timingFunction = timingFunctionForKeyframeAtIndex(startKeyframeIndex.value()))
1558 transformedDistance = timingFunction->transformTime(intervalDistance, rangeDuration);
1559 }
1560 }
1561
1562 // 18. Return the result of applying the interpolation procedure defined by the animation type of the target property, to the values of the target
1563 // property specified on the two keyframes in interval endpoints taking the first such value as Vstart and the second as Vend and using transformed
1564 // distance as the interpolation parameter p.
1565 auto startStyle = !startKeyframeIndex ? &targetStyle : m_blendingKeyframes[startKeyframeIndex.value()].style();
1566 auto endStyle = !endKeyframeIndex ? &targetStyle : m_blendingKeyframes[endKeyframeIndex.value()].style();
1567 CSSPropertyAnimation::blendProperties(this, cssPropertyId, targetStyle, *startStyle, *endStyle, transformedDistance);
1568 }
1569}
1570
1571TimingFunction* KeyframeEffect::timingFunctionForKeyframeAtIndex(size_t index) const
1572{
1573 if (!m_parsedKeyframes.isEmpty()) {
1574 if (index >= m_parsedKeyframes.size())
1575 return nullptr;
1576 return m_parsedKeyframes[index].timingFunction.get();
1577 }
1578
1579 auto effectAnimation = animation();
1580 if (is<DeclarativeAnimation>(effectAnimation)) {
1581 // If we're dealing with a CSS Animation, the timing function is specified either on the keyframe itself.
1582 if (is<CSSAnimation>(effectAnimation)) {
1583 if (index >= m_blendingKeyframes.size())
1584 return nullptr;
1585 if (auto* timingFunction = m_blendingKeyframes[index].timingFunction())
1586 return timingFunction;
1587 }
1588
1589 // Failing that, or for a CSS Transition, the timing function is inherited from the backing Animation object.
1590 return downcast<DeclarativeAnimation>(effectAnimation)->backingAnimation().timingFunction();
1591 }
1592
1593 return nullptr;
1594}
1595
1596bool KeyframeEffect::canBeAccelerated() const
1597{
1598 return m_acceleratedPropertiesState != AcceleratedProperties::None && !m_someKeyframesUseStepsTimingFunction && !is<StepsTimingFunction>(timingFunction());
1599}
1600
1601void KeyframeEffect::updateAcceleratedActions()
1602{
1603 if (!canBeAccelerated()) {
1604 // In the case where this animation is actively targeting a transform-related property and yet
1605 // cannot be accelerated, we must notify the effect stack such that any running accelerated
1606 // transform-related animation targeting this element reverts to running non-accelerated.
1607 if (isTargetingTransformRelatedProperty()
1608 && animation()->playState() == WebAnimation::PlayState::Running
1609 && getComputedTiming().phase == AnimationEffectPhase::Active) {
1610 ASSERT(targetStyleable());
1611 ASSERT(targetStyleable()->keyframeEffectStack());
1612 targetStyleable()->keyframeEffectStack()->stopAcceleratingTransformRelatedProperties(UseAcceleratedAction::Yes);
1613 }
1614 return;
1615 }
1616
1617 auto computedTiming = getComputedTiming();
1618
1619 // If we're not already running accelerated, the only thing we're interested in is whether we need to start the animation
1620 // which we need to do once we're in the active phase. Otherwise, there's no change in accelerated state to consider.
1621 bool isActive = computedTiming.phase == AnimationEffectPhase::Active;
1622 if (m_runningAccelerated == RunningAccelerated::NotStarted) {
1623 if (isActive && animation()->playState() == WebAnimation::PlayState::Running)
1624 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::Play);
1625 return;
1626 }
1627
1628 // If we're no longer active, we need to remove the accelerated animation.
1629 if (!isActive) {
1630 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::Stop);
1631 return;
1632 }
1633
1634 auto playState = animation()->playState();
1635 // The only thing left to consider is whether we need to pause or resume the animation following a change of play-state.
1636 if (playState == WebAnimation::PlayState::Paused) {
1637 if (m_lastRecordedAcceleratedAction != AcceleratedAction::Pause) {
1638 if (m_lastRecordedAcceleratedAction == AcceleratedAction::Stop)
1639 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::Play);
1640 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::Pause);
1641 }
1642 } else if (playState == WebAnimation::PlayState::Running && isActive) {
1643 if (m_lastRecordedAcceleratedAction != AcceleratedAction::Play)
1644 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::Play);
1645 }
1646}
1647
1648void KeyframeEffect::addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction action)
1649{
1650 if (action == m_lastRecordedAcceleratedAction)
1651 return;
1652
1653 if (action == AcceleratedAction::Stop)
1654 m_pendingAcceleratedActions.clear();
1655 m_pendingAcceleratedActions.append(action);
1656 if (action != AcceleratedAction::UpdateTiming && action != AcceleratedAction::TransformChange)
1657 m_lastRecordedAcceleratedAction = action;
1658 animation()->acceleratedStateDidChange();
1659}
1660
1661void KeyframeEffect::animationDidTick()
1662{
1663 invalidate();
1664 updateAcceleratedActions();
1665}
1666
1667void KeyframeEffect::animationDidPlay()
1668{
1669 if (m_acceleratedPropertiesState != AcceleratedProperties::None)
1670 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::Play);
1671}
1672
1673void KeyframeEffect::animationDidChangeTimingProperties()
1674{
1675 computeSomeKeyframesUseStepsTimingFunction();
1676
1677 if (isRunningAccelerated() || isAboutToRunAccelerated())
1678 addPendingAcceleratedAction(canBeAccelerated() ? AcceleratedAction::UpdateTiming : AcceleratedAction::Stop);
1679 else if (canBeAccelerated())
1680 m_runningAccelerated = RunningAccelerated::NotStarted;
1681}
1682
1683void KeyframeEffect::transformRelatedPropertyDidChange()
1684{
1685 ASSERT(isRunningAcceleratedTransformRelatedAnimation());
1686 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::TransformChange);
1687}
1688
1689void KeyframeEffect::animationWasCanceled()
1690{
1691 if (isRunningAccelerated() || isAboutToRunAccelerated())
1692 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::Stop);
1693}
1694
1695void KeyframeEffect::willChangeRenderer()
1696{
1697 if (isRunningAccelerated() || isAboutToRunAccelerated())
1698 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::Stop);
1699}
1700
1701void KeyframeEffect::animationSuspensionStateDidChange(bool animationIsSuspended)
1702{
1703 if (isRunningAccelerated() || isAboutToRunAccelerated())
1704 addPendingAcceleratedAction(animationIsSuspended ? AcceleratedAction::Pause : AcceleratedAction::Play);
1705}
1706
1707OptionSet<AcceleratedActionApplicationResult> KeyframeEffect::applyPendingAcceleratedActions()
1708{
1709 OptionSet<AcceleratedActionApplicationResult> result;
1710
1711 // Once an accelerated animation has been committed, we no longer want to force a layout.
1712 // This should have been performed by a call to forceLayoutIfNeeded() prior to applying
1713 // pending accelerated actions.
1714 m_needsForcedLayout = false;
1715
1716 if (m_pendingAcceleratedActions.isEmpty())
1717 return result;
1718
1719 auto* renderer = this->renderer();
1720 if (!renderer || !renderer->isComposited()) {
1721 // The renderer may no longer be composited because the accelerated animation ended before we had a chance to update it,
1722 // in which case if we asked for the animation to stop, we can discard the current set of accelerated actions.
1723 if (m_lastRecordedAcceleratedAction == AcceleratedAction::Stop) {
1724 m_pendingAcceleratedActions.clear();
1725 m_runningAccelerated = RunningAccelerated::NotStarted;
1726 }
1727 return result;
1728 }
1729
1730 auto pendingAcceleratedActions = m_pendingAcceleratedActions;
1731 m_pendingAcceleratedActions.clear();
1732
1733 // To simplify the code we use a default of 0s for an unresolved current time since for a Stop action that is acceptable.
1734 auto timeOffset = animation()->currentTime().value_or(0_s).seconds() - delay().seconds();
1735
1736 auto startAnimation = [&]() -> RunningAccelerated {
1737 if (m_runningAccelerated == RunningAccelerated::Yes)
1738 renderer->animationFinished(m_blendingKeyframes.animationName());
1739
1740 if (!m_blendingKeyframes.hasImplicitKeyframes())
1741 return renderer->startAnimation(timeOffset, backingAnimationForCompositedRenderer(), m_blendingKeyframes) ? RunningAccelerated::Yes : RunningAccelerated::No;
1742
1743 ASSERT(m_target);
1744
1745 auto* lastStyleChangeEventStyle = m_target->lastStyleChangeEventStyle(m_pseudoId);
1746 ASSERT(lastStyleChangeEventStyle);
1747
1748 KeyframeList explicitKeyframes(m_blendingKeyframes.animationName());
1749 explicitKeyframes.copyKeyframes(m_blendingKeyframes);
1750 explicitKeyframes.fillImplicitKeyframes(*m_target, m_target->styleResolver(), lastStyleChangeEventStyle, nullptr);
1751 return renderer->startAnimation(timeOffset, backingAnimationForCompositedRenderer(), explicitKeyframes) ? RunningAccelerated::Yes : RunningAccelerated::No;
1752 };
1753
1754 for (const auto& action : pendingAcceleratedActions) {
1755 switch (action) {
1756 case AcceleratedAction::Play:
1757 m_runningAccelerated = startAnimation();
1758 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Animations, stream << "KeyframeEffect " << this << " applyPendingAcceleratedActions " << m_blendingKeyframes.animationName() << " Play, started accelerated: " << (m_runningAccelerated == RunningAccelerated::Yes));
1759 if (m_runningAccelerated == RunningAccelerated::No) {
1760 m_lastRecordedAcceleratedAction = AcceleratedAction::Stop;
1761 if (isTargetingTransformRelatedProperty())
1762 result.add(AcceleratedActionApplicationResult::TransformRelatedAnimationCannotBeAccelerated);
1763 return result;
1764 }
1765 break;
1766 case AcceleratedAction::Pause:
1767 renderer->animationPaused(timeOffset, m_blendingKeyframes.animationName());
1768 break;
1769 case AcceleratedAction::UpdateTiming:
1770 m_runningAccelerated = startAnimation();
1771 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Animations, stream << "KeyframeEffect " << this << " applyPendingAcceleratedActions " << m_blendingKeyframes.animationName() << " UpdateTiming, started accelerated: " << (m_runningAccelerated == RunningAccelerated::Yes));
1772 if (animation()->playState() == WebAnimation::PlayState::Paused)
1773 renderer->animationPaused(timeOffset, m_blendingKeyframes.animationName());
1774 break;
1775 case AcceleratedAction::Stop:
1776 ASSERT(document());
1777 renderer->animationFinished(m_blendingKeyframes.animationName());
1778 if (!document()->renderTreeBeingDestroyed())
1779 m_target->invalidateStyleAndLayerComposition();
1780 m_runningAccelerated = canBeAccelerated() ? RunningAccelerated::NotStarted : RunningAccelerated::No;
1781 break;
1782 case AcceleratedAction::TransformChange:
1783 renderer->transformRelatedPropertyDidChange();
1784 break;
1785 }
1786 }
1787
1788 if (m_runningAccelerated == RunningAccelerated::No && isTargetingTransformRelatedProperty())
1789 result.add(AcceleratedActionApplicationResult::TransformRelatedAnimationCannotBeAccelerated);
1790
1791 return result;
1792}
1793
1794void KeyframeEffect::stopAcceleratingTransformRelatedProperties(UseAcceleratedAction useAcceleratedAction)
1795{
1796 if (!isRunningAcceleratedTransformRelatedAnimation())
1797 return;
1798
1799 if (useAcceleratedAction == UseAcceleratedAction::Yes) {
1800 addPendingAcceleratedAction(AcceleratedAction::Stop);
1801 return;
1802 }
1803
1804 auto* renderer = this->renderer();
1805 if (!renderer || !renderer->isComposited())
1806 return;
1807
1808 ASSERT(document());
1809 renderer->animationFinished(m_blendingKeyframes.animationName());
1810 if (!document()->renderTreeBeingDestroyed())
1811 m_target->invalidateStyleAndLayerComposition();
1812
1813 m_runningAccelerated = RunningAccelerated::No;
1814}
1815
1816Ref<const Animation> KeyframeEffect::backingAnimationForCompositedRenderer() const
1817{
1818 auto effectAnimation = animation();
1819
1820 // FIXME: The iterationStart and endDelay AnimationEffectTiming properties do not have
1821 // corresponding Animation properties.
1822 auto animation = Animation::create();
1823 animation->setDuration(iterationDuration().seconds());
1824 animation->setDelay(delay().seconds());
1825 animation->setIterationCount(iterations());
1826 animation->setTimingFunction(timingFunction()->clone());
1827 animation->setPlaybackRate(effectAnimation->playbackRate());
1828
1829 switch (fill()) {
1830 case FillMode::None:
1831 case FillMode::Auto:
1832 animation->setFillMode(AnimationFillMode::None);
1833 break;
1834 case FillMode::Backwards:
1835 animation->setFillMode(AnimationFillMode::Backwards);
1836 break;
1837 case FillMode::Forwards:
1838 animation->setFillMode(AnimationFillMode::Forwards);
1839 break;
1840 case FillMode::Both:
1841 animation->setFillMode(AnimationFillMode::Both);
1842 break;
1843 }
1844
1845 switch (direction()) {
1846 case PlaybackDirection::Normal:
1847 animation->setDirection(Animation::AnimationDirectionNormal);
1848 break;
1849 case PlaybackDirection::Alternate:
1850 animation->setDirection(Animation::AnimationDirectionAlternate);
1851 break;
1852 case PlaybackDirection::Reverse:
1853 animation->setDirection(Animation::AnimationDirectionReverse);
1854 break;
1855 case PlaybackDirection::AlternateReverse:
1856 animation->setDirection(Animation::AnimationDirectionAlternateReverse);
1857 break;
1858 }
1859
1860 // In the case of CSS Animations, we must set the default timing function for keyframes to match
1861 // the current value set for animation-timing-function on the target element which affects only
1862 // keyframes and not the animation-wide timing.
1863 if (is<CSSAnimation>(effectAnimation))
1864 animation->setDefaultTimingFunctionForKeyframes(downcast<CSSAnimation>(effectAnimation)->backingAnimation().timingFunction());
1865
1866 return animation;
1867}

1885
1886bool KeyframeEffect::computeExtentOfTransformAnimation(LayoutRect& bounds) const
1887{
1888 ASSERT(m_blendingKeyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyTransform));
1889
1890 if (!is<RenderBox>(renderer()))
1891 return true; // Non-boxes don't get transformed;
1892
1893 auto& box = downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer());
1894 auto rendererBox = snapRectToDevicePixels(box.borderBoxRect(), box.document().deviceScaleFactor());
1895
1896 LayoutRect cumulativeBounds;
1897
1898 auto addStyleToCumulativeBounds = [&](const RenderStyle* style) -> bool {
1899 auto keyframeBounds = bounds;
1900
1901 bool canCompute;
1902 if (transformFunctionListsMatch())
1903 canCompute = computeTransformedExtentViaTransformList(rendererBox, *style, keyframeBounds);
1904 else
1905 canCompute = computeTransformedExtentViaMatrix(rendererBox, *style, keyframeBounds);
1906
1907 if (!canCompute)
1908 return false;
1909
1910 cumulativeBounds.unite(keyframeBounds);
1911 return true;
1912 };
1913
1914 for (const auto& keyframe : m_blendingKeyframes.keyframes()) {
1915 const auto* keyframeStyle = keyframe.style();
1916
1917 // FIXME: maybe for declarative animations we always say it's true for the first and last keyframe.
1918 if (!keyframe.containsProperty(CSSPropertyTransform)) {
1919 // If the first keyframe is missing transform style, use the current style.
1920 if (!keyframe.key())
1921 keyframeStyle = &box.style();
1922 else
1923 continue;
1924 }
1925
1926 if (!addStyleToCumulativeBounds(keyframeStyle))
1927 return false;
1928 }
1929
1930 if (m_blendingKeyframes.hasImplicitKeyframes()) {
1931 if (!addStyleToCumulativeBounds(&box.style()))
1932 return false;
1933 }
1934
1935 bounds = cumulativeBounds;
1936 return true;
1937}
1938
1939static bool containsRotation(const Vector<RefPtr<TransformOperation>>& operations)
1940{
1941 for (const auto& operation : operations) {
1942 if (operation->type() == TransformOperation::ROTATE)
1943 return true;
1944 }
1945 return false;
1946}
1947
1948bool KeyframeEffect::computeTransformedExtentViaTransformList(const FloatRect& rendererBox, const RenderStyle& style, LayoutRect& bounds) const
1949{
1950 FloatRect floatBounds = bounds;
1951 FloatPoint transformOrigin;
1952
1953 bool applyTransformOrigin = containsRotation(style.transform().operations()) || style.transform().affectedByTransformOrigin();
1954 if (applyTransformOrigin) {
1955 transformOrigin = rendererBox.location() + floatPointForLengthPoint(style.transformOriginXY(), rendererBox.size());
1956 // Ignore transformOriginZ because we'll bail if we encounter any 3D transforms.
1957 floatBounds.moveBy(-transformOrigin);
1958 }
1959
1960 for (const auto& operation : style.transform().operations()) {
1961 if (operation->type() == TransformOperation::ROTATE) {
1962 // For now, just treat this as a full rotation. This could take angle into account to reduce inflation.
1963 floatBounds = boundsOfRotatingRect(floatBounds);
1964 } else {
1965 TransformationMatrix transform;
1966 operation->apply(transform, rendererBox.size());
1967 if (!transform.isAffine())
1968 return false;
1969
1970 if (operation->type() == TransformOperation::MATRIX || operation->type() == TransformOperation::MATRIX_3D) {
1971 TransformationMatrix::Decomposed2Type toDecomp;
1972 transform.decompose2(toDecomp);
1973 // Any rotation prevents us from using a simple start/end rect union.
1974 if (toDecomp.angle)
1975 return false;
1976 }
1977
1978 floatBounds = transform.mapRect(floatBounds);
1979 }
1980 }
1981
1982 if (applyTransformOrigin)
1983 floatBounds.moveBy(transformOrigin);
1984
1985 bounds = LayoutRect(floatBounds);
1986 return true;
1987}
1988
1989bool KeyframeEffect::computeTransformedExtentViaMatrix(const FloatRect& rendererBox, const RenderStyle& style, LayoutRect& bounds) const
1990{
1991 TransformationMatrix transform;
1992 style.applyTransform(transform, rendererBox);
1993 if (!transform.isAffine())
1994 return false;
1995
1996 TransformationMatrix::Decomposed2Type fromDecomp;
1997 transform.decompose2(fromDecomp);
1998 // Any rotation prevents us from using a simple start/end rect union.
1999 if (fromDecomp.angle)
2000 return false;
2001
2002 bounds = LayoutRect(transform.mapRect(bounds));
2003 return true;
2004}

2007{
2008 return m_blendingKeyframesSource == BlendingKeyframesSource::WebAnimation && targetsPseudoElement();
2009}
2010
2011std::optional<double> KeyframeEffect::progressUntilNextStep(double iterationProgress) const
2012{
2013 ASSERT(iterationProgress >= 0 && iterationProgress <= 1);
2014
2015 if (auto progress = AnimationEffect::progressUntilNextStep(iterationProgress))
2016 return progress;
2017
2018 if (!is<LinearTimingFunction>(timingFunction()) || !m_someKeyframesUseStepsTimingFunction)
2019 return std::nullopt;
2020
2021 if (m_blendingKeyframes.isEmpty())
2022 return std::nullopt;
2023
2024 auto progressUntilNextStepInInterval = [iterationProgress](double intervalStartProgress, double intervalEndProgress, TimingFunction* timingFunction) -> std::optional<double> {
2025 if (!is<StepsTimingFunction>(timingFunction))
2026 return std::nullopt;
2027
2028 auto numberOfSteps = downcast<StepsTimingFunction>(*timingFunction).numberOfSteps();
2029 auto intervalProgress = intervalEndProgress - intervalStartProgress;
2030 auto iterationProgressMappedToCurrentInterval = (iterationProgress - intervalStartProgress) / intervalProgress;
2031 auto nextStepProgress = ceil(iterationProgressMappedToCurrentInterval * numberOfSteps) / numberOfSteps;
2032 return (nextStepProgress - iterationProgressMappedToCurrentInterval) * intervalProgress;
2033 };
2034
2035 for (size_t i = 0; i < m_blendingKeyframes.size(); ++i) {
2036 auto intervalEndProgress = m_blendingKeyframes[i].key();
2037 // We can stop once we find a keyframe for which the progress is more than the provided iteration progress.
2038 if (intervalEndProgress <= iterationProgress)
2039 continue;
2040
2041 // In case we're on the first keyframe, then this means we are dealing with an implicit 0% keyframe.
2042 // This will be a linear timing function unless we're dealing with a CSS Animation which might have
2043 // the default timing function for its keyframes defined on its backing Animation object.
2044 if (!i) {
2045 if (is<CSSAnimation>(animation()))
2046 return progressUntilNextStepInInterval(0, intervalEndProgress, downcast<DeclarativeAnimation>(*animation()).backingAnimation().timingFunction());
2047 return std::nullopt;
2048 }
2049
2050 return progressUntilNextStepInInterval(m_blendingKeyframes[i - 1].key(), intervalEndProgress, timingFunctionForKeyframeAtIndex(i - 1));
2051 }
2052
2053 // If we end up here, then this means we are dealing with an implicit 100% keyframe.
2054 // This will be a linear timing function unless we're dealing with a CSS Animation which might have
2055 // the default timing function for its keyframes defined on its backing Animation object.
2056 auto& lastExplicitKeyframe = m_blendingKeyframes[m_blendingKeyframes.size() - 1];
2057 if (is<CSSAnimation>(animation()))
2058 return progressUntilNextStepInInterval(lastExplicitKeyframe.key(), 1, downcast<DeclarativeAnimation>(*animation()).backingAnimation().timingFunction());
2059
2060 // In any other case, we are not dealing with an interval with a steps() timing function.
2061 return std::nullopt;
2062}
2063
2064Seconds KeyframeEffect::timeToNextTick() const
2065{
2066 auto timing = getBasicTiming();
2067 switch (timing.phase) {
2068 case AnimationEffectPhase::Before:
2069 // The effect is in its "before" phase, in this case we can wait until it enters its "active" phase.
2070 return delay() - *timing.localTime;
2071 case AnimationEffectPhase::Active: {
2072 auto doesNotAffectStyles = m_blendingKeyframes.isEmpty() || m_blendingKeyframes.properties().isEmpty();
2073 auto completelyAcceleratedAndRunning = isCompletelyAccelerated() && isRunningAccelerated();
2074 if (doesNotAffectStyles || completelyAcceleratedAndRunning) {
2075 // In the case of fully accelerated running effects and effects that don't actually target any CSS property,
2076 // we do not have a need to invalidate styles.
2077 if (is<CSSAnimation>(animation())) {
2078 // However, CSS Animations need to trigger "animationiteration" events, in this case we must wait until the next iteration.
2079 if (auto iterationProgress = getComputedTiming().simpleIterationProgress)
2080 return iterationDuration() * (1 - *iterationProgress);
2081 }
2082 // Other running effects in the "active" phase can wait until they end.
2083 return endTime() - *timing.localTime;
2084 }
2085 if (auto iterationProgress = getComputedTiming().simpleIterationProgress) {
2086 // In case we're in a range that uses a steps() timing function, we can compute the time until the next step starts.
2087 if (auto progressUntilNextStep = this->progressUntilNextStep(*iterationProgress))
2088 return iterationDuration() * *progressUntilNextStep;
2089 }
2090 // Other effects in the "active" phase will need to update their animated value at the immediate next opportunity.
2091 return 0_s;
2092 }
2093 case AnimationEffectPhase::After:
2094 // The effect is in its after phase, which means it will no longer update its value, so it doens't need a tick.
2095 return Seconds::infinity();
2096 case AnimationEffectPhase::Idle:
2097 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2098 return Seconds::infinity();
2099 }
2100
2101 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2102 return Seconds::infinity();
2103}
